    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate leaning heavily on **Jackson Merrill**, whose score of 75.26 is the undisputed highlight of the roster. Facing Ryan Feltner (xERA 4.63) in a highly favorable park, **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a massive 14% park boost and 15% SP skill advantage, making him our primary engine for both AVG and RBI production. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** also presents a strong 70.48 efficiency score; he is primed for a breakout against JR Ritchie, bolstered by a significant 14% platoon edge that makes him a must-start in the MI slot today. While **Kyle Tucker** faces a daunting matchup against the elite Logan Webb, his pedigree and the small 100% stolen base window provided by Webb\u2019s delivery pace keep him in the lineup, though his score of 54.02 reflects the clear risk inherent in facing a top-tier arm.\n\nThe toughest call of the morning involved keeping **Andy Pages** on the bench with a 41.93 score. He finished just outside the starting rotation, edged out by the superior park and platoon dynamics favoring **Dominic Smith** and **Heliot Ramos**. While **Andy Pages** remains a high-upside asset, the combination of facing a sub-3.20 xERA pitcher and the increased defensive efficiency of his opponent's catcher (1.86s pop time) dragged his score below our threshold for starting consideration. We are also monitoring **Luis Robert Jr.** closely; while his score of 42.86 is suppressed by a brutal 16% SP skill penalty against Joe Ryan, the aggressive 4% SB boost from Ryan's slow delivery speed mandates his inclusion for our pursuit of steals.\n\nManagers should remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status across the board, as the official batting orders are the primary variable for our score projections. Notably, **Marcell Ozuna** is a high-risk play today against Jacob deGrom. Despite a 43.29 efficiency score\u2014aided slightly by a 4% order boost\u2014his BvP history (44 PA) against deGrom is unfavorable, 